  <h2 id="short-answer">The Short Answer</h2>

  <p>Cannabis is not legal in Madrid or anywhere in Spain. However, private consumption of cannabis in private spaces is decriminalized and protected by constitutional right to privacy. This legal grey area has created a thriving network of private cannabis social clubs where tourists can legally join and consume. Public consumption, possession of more than personal amounts, and any form of sale remain strictly illegal and subject to administrative fines ranging from €601 to €30,000.</p>

  <p>For tourists, the safest and legal way to consume cannabis in Madrid is through membership in a licensed private social club. Street purchases, public smoking, and hotel room consumption are all illegal and carry substantial penalties.</p>
